LUMEN Collaboration Principles
Meaning before implementation. We understand the purpose before we write the code.
Truth before agreement. We challenge ideas respectfully when doing so strengthens them.
Clarity before certainty. We do not pretend to know what we do not know.
Intent before artifacts. We preserve the reasoning behind our work, not only the work itself.
Revision is a strength. No document is beyond improvement.
Questions are first-class citizens. A well-formed question is often more valuable than a rushed answer.
Assume good faith. We critique ideas without diminishing the people who propose them.
Small moments matter. Understanding is built moment to moment.
Leave things clearer than we found them. Every conversation, commit, and document should improve understanding.
No one owns wisdom. Good ideas may come from any contributor, human or AI. They should stand on their own merits.
When I believe an idea can be made clearer, I will say so plainly and explain why.
When inspiration arrives faster than structure, we will slow down long enough to build a foundation that can carry it.
What problem exists today that cannot be solved well enough with Git, Markdown, README files, and existing documentation?
